cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI 

This paper deals with 3D reconstruction from a single RGB image, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the issue of occlusion, which is a common problem in graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves using a predicted silhouette to guide the reconstruction process, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
